# Frontend Rules

## React

* Prefer functional components.
* Keep components small.
* Avoid components longer than ~250 lines.
* Extract reusable UI.
* Avoid prop drilling when better alternatives exist.

---

## Next.js

Default to Server Components.

Only use:

"use client"

when required for:

* state
* effects
* browser APIs
* event handlers

Do not make components client components unnecessarily.

---

## State Management

Prefer:

1. local state
2. URL state
3. server state
4. global state

Do not introduce global state without justification.

---

## Tailwind CSS

Use Tailwind utilities.

Prefer spacing scale:

p-4
p-6
p-8

instead of:

p-[19px]

Avoid arbitrary values unless absolutely necessary.

---

## Colors

Never hardcode colors. Use design tokens from `src/app/globals.css`.

**Canonical token names (Material 3):**

```
bg-background / bg-surface-container-lowest
text-on-surface / text-on-surface-variant
text-secondary
bg-primary / text-on-primary
bg-primary-container / text-on-primary-container
border-outline-variant
```

**Important:** `primary` is `#006c4b`. `#03a575` is `primary-container` (hover states, chips).

Legacy aliases like `text-foreground` map to `text-on-surface` — prefer M3 names in new code.

---

## Typography

Use the typography scale.

Prefer:

text-sm
text-base
text-lg
text-xl
text-2xl

Avoid arbitrary font sizes.

---

## Layout

Prefer:

container
mx-auto
max-w-7xl
grid
flex
gap

Avoid fixed widths.

Always build mobile first.

---

## Images

Use Next.js Image.

Always include meaningful alt text.

Optimize images.

---

## Icons

Use lucide-react.

Avoid inline SVG unless required.

---

## Accessibility

Always:

* proper labels
* keyboard navigation
* aria attributes
* focus states
* sufficient contrast

Decorative icons:

aria-hidden="true"

---

## SEO

Every page should include:

* one H1
* proper heading hierarchy
* semantic landmarks
* metadata
* descriptive alt text

---

## HTML

Prefer semantic elements:

header

nav

main

section

article

aside

footer

Avoid unnecessary div nesting.

---

## Styling

Never use inline styles.

Keep Tailwind classes readable.


---

## Responsive

Every component should support:

* Mobile
* Tablet
* Laptop
* Desktop

Never assume desktop-first layouts.

---

## Review Checklist

Before finishing:

✓ Responsive

✓ Accessible

✓ Semantic

✓ SEO-friendly

✓ Uses design tokens

✓ No duplicated JSX

✓ Clean React code
